---
title: Pan-Seared Chicken with Tomato-Barley Hash & Charred Broccoli
description: Nutty, wholesome barley makes a great blank canvas. Mild chives, floral lemon zest and crunchy almonds help create a hash that's perfect with juicy chicken. Allowing broccoli to develop color in the oven gives it extra depth of flavor - a final squeeze of lemon makes it even more delicious.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5540ec8f6ced6eed7a8b4567.
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/5540ec8f6ced6eed7a8b4567.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 822 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  protein: 55 g
  fiber: 21 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pan-seared-chicken-5540ec8f6ced6eed7a8b4567
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a #medium pot{}, bring 3 cups of water to a boil
with a large pinch of @salt{}. Once boiling, add the @barley{3/4%cup} to the
pot and cook for about ~{30-35%minutes}, until tender. Drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, cut the @broccoli florets{1%head} into florets. Zest and halve the
@lemon{1}. Finely chop the @chives{1%bunch}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}.
Halve, seed, and core the @tomato{1}, then dice.

Toss the broccoli florets on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and
a pinch of salt and @black pepper{}. Place in the oven and roast for
~{20-25%minutes}, until lightly charred. Then, finish with a squeeze of lemon.

While the broccoli roasts, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Season the @chicken breasts{2} on both sides with salt and
pepper. Add the chicken to the pan and sear for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until
golden brown but not yet cooked through. Transfer to the baking sheet in the
oven to finish cooking for ~{6-8%minutes}, until juices run clear when pierced
with a knife. Remove from the oven and set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in the same pan, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} over medium heat.
Add the diced tomato and cook, stirring for about ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened.
Add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with salt and
pepper.

Add the cooked barley to the tomato mixture along with the lemon zest, chives,
@veggie stock concentrate{1}, and 1/4 cup water. Toss to combine.

Thinly slice the chicken against the grain. Serve atop the tomato-barley hash
with charred broccoli to the side. Sprinkle with the @almonds{1%ounce}(sliced)
and enjoy!

> Nutty, wholesome barley makes a great blank canvas. Mild chives, floral lemon
> zest and crunchy almonds help create a hash that's perfect with juicy chicken.
> Allowing broccoli to develop color in the oven gives it extra depth of flavor -
> a final squeeze of lemon makes it even more delicious.